title: One dead and three missing as boat carrying British tourists overturns on Italian lake
description: A boat carrying at least 20 tourists and crew members has overturned in a whirlwind on Italy's Lake Maggiore.

title: Erdogan has proved his critics wrong and outmanoeuvred his toughest challengers
description: The man who revels in his image as Turkey's strongman took an early lead almost as soon as polls closed in the second round of voting for President.

title: Protest planned against Roger Waters' concert over 'Nazi costume'
description: A memorial ceremony and rally are to be held in protest against a concert by Pink Lloyd star Roger Waters in Frankfurt on Sunday night.

title: Erdogan declared winner in Turkey presidential election
description: Recep Tayyip Erdogan has won the presidential run-off election, with leaders from around the world congratulating him.

title: Venice police investigating bright green liquid in Grand Canal
description: Police in Venice have launched an investigation into the source of a phosphorescent green liquid patch that has appeared in the city's famed Grand Canal.

title: Plane passenger could face years in jail for 'opening door mid-flight'
description: A plane passenger could face up to 10 years in prison if he is found guilty of violating aviation security law by opening an emergency exit mid-flight.

title: Husband unaware pregnant wife and baby killed in Sudan shooting
description: Men in crisp white thobes sit on mats under a leafy thorn tree carefully cutting pieces of white material.

title: PSG goalkeeper Sergio Rico in intensive care
description: Paris St Germain goalkeeper Sergio Rico is in intensive care following a riding accident.

title: Olympic wrestlers who 'broke barricades' at sexual harassment protest detained
description: Several of India's top wrestlers were detained by police after protests against a federation chief intensified over sexual harassment allegations.

title: Ancient tombs and mummification workshops unearthed in Egypt
description: Ancient tombs and workshops used for mummification have been unveiled near the Egyptian capital of Cairo.

title: Two million litres of water drained from reservoir in search for phone
description: An Indian government official has been suspended after ordering a reservoir to be drained so he could find his phone.

title: Turks head to the polls to decide if Erdogan takes rule into third decade
description: Turkey goes to the polls today for a presidential run-off that could see Recep Tayyip Erdogan extend his rule into a third decade.

title: Joe Biden and Kevin McCarthy reach 'tentative deal' on raising US debt ceiling - sources
description: President Joe Biden and House Speaker Kevin McCarthy have reached a "tentative deal" on raising the US debt ceiling, according to sources in Washington.
